{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Reduce VAT to 5% on Hydrotreated Vegetable Oil (HVO), an alternative to Diesel",
        "additional_details": "It\u2019s green, proven to cut up to 90% of net CO2 emissions and it can be made in the UK but it\u2019s charged at 20% VAT. So let\u2019s encourage use and reduce VAT to 5%. A straightforward VAT reduction from 20% to 5% will bring it into closer parity with diesel prices. If home-based charging for electric vehicles is charged only 5% VAT, why should HVO be stuck at 20%?",
        "background": "HVO is a viable alternative fuel to Diesel. Using it we believe that we can reuse our existing fuel infrastructure and vehicles and make use of a product to support an orderly transition to net zero in realistic timescales without reliance on imported electric vehicles made overseas. ",
